{"id":"remeth","term":"Remeth","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Another form of Ramah (q.v.) or Ramoth (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 6:73\">1 Chr. 6:73</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 19:21\">Josh. 19:21</a>), and probably also of Jarmuth (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 21:29\">Josh. 21:29</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 6:73","Joshua 19:21","Joshua 21:29"]}